record_data.record_plain_text:
Mississippi Power Company hereby incorporates Southern's Market Based Rate Tariff as filed by Alabama Power Company, which is referenced as:
Tariff Title (Tariff Database) - Market Based Rate Tariff
Market Based Rate Tariff, Southern's Tariff Volume No. 4

Cover Page
Company: Mississippi Power Company Designated Filing Company: Alabama Power Company Service Providers: Alabama Power Company, Georgia Power Company, Gulf Power Company, Mississippi Power Company, and Southern Power Company (collectively, "Southern") Tariff Title (Tariff Database): Market Based Rate Tariff Tariff Description: Market Based Rate Tariff, Southern's Tariff Volume No. 4

Mississippi Power Company hereby incorporates the FERC FPA Electric Tariff described below and filed by Alabama Power Company with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission on February 12, 2021 and all future amendments and modifications thereto, and hereby files this concurrence in lieu of the filing of the tariff specified below.
1. Designated Filing Company of the Tariff Record Incorporated by Reference: Alabama Power Company 2. Tariff Title Incorporated by Reference: Market Based Rate Tariff, Rate Schedule No. 1011, Southeast EEM Agreement 3. Tariff Program/Regulated Industry: FERC FPA Electric Tariff 4. No Limitations: All versions of the agreement 5. Description of Tariff: Southeast Energy Exchange Market Agreement between Alabama Power Company; Georgia Power Company; Mississippi Power Company; Associated Electric Cooperative, Inc.; Dalton Utilities; Dominion Energy South Carolina, Inc.; Duke Energy Carolinas, LLC; Duke Energy Progress, LLC; Louisville Gas and Electric Company; Kentucky Utilities Company; North Carolina Municipal Power Agency Number 1; North Carolina Electric Membership Corporation; PowerSouth Energy Cooperative; and Tennessee Valley Authority, dated December 28, 2020
record_data.filing_title: Response to Second Deficiency Letter regarding Southeast EEM Agreement
